 including web authoring  marketing  graphic design  information technologies  journalism  user experience  video  photography  and social media  Prior to her appointment at VMI  Crossman held a teaching assistant position for Media Foundations at New School University  NY  As the Assistant to the CFO at the Corcoran Gallery of Art  Crossman managed the office  worked with independent vendors and produced various print materials  At the Smithsonian Institution Archives  she coordinated the production of marketing materials  the SIA Annual Report  wrote and edited histories for the Guide to the Smithsonian Archives  supervised the Archives library as well as accessioned and managed official records for offices of General Council  Public Affairs  National Air and Space Museum  Smithsonian Science Information Exchange and Smithsonian Research Foundation  In addition  she was part of the team to create significant public exhibits at the Smithsonian Institute Archives  James Monroe Museum and Mary Washington College  M A  Media Studies  New School University  NY B A  Art History  Mary Washington College  VA Curatorial Intern at James Monroe Museum and Memorial Library  VA Assistant to Director  Mary Washington College  DuPont Galleries  VA VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Lt  Col  Kate Crossman  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu Abo